use V6evalRemote;

rOpen() || goto error;

$rOpt_timeout=10 if ! defined($rOpt_timeout);

$cmd = "/bin/rm -rf /tmp/ipsec.conf\r";
$cmd .= "/usr/sbin/tiny_ipsec_reset\r";
$cmd .= "\cD";

rLogin($rOpt_timeout) || goto error;
rCommand($cmd, $rOpt_timeout) || goto error;
rLogout($rOpt_timeout) || goto error;

rClose();

exit($V6evalRemote::exitPass);

error:
    rClose();
    exit($V6evalRemote::exitFAIL);

########################################################################
__END__

=head1 NAME

ipsecClearAll.rmt - clear all SAD and SPD

=head1 SYNOPSIS

ipsecClearAll.rmt [-commonoption ...]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

B<ipsecClearAll.rmt> clears all security policy database (SPD) and security association database (SAD).
Do ``perldoc V6evalRemote'' for common options.

=head1 RETURN VALUES

The B<ipsecClearAll.rmt> exits with one of the following values:

 0  command completed successfully
 1  command failed

=head1 SEE ALSO

perldoc V6evalRemote

